[2]
Date: Mon, 19 May 1997 08:45:35 -0500
From: ertl@wista.wistar.upenn.edu (Ertl, Hildegund)
The killed vaccine won't harm the raccoons. The most extensively tested
vaccine for raccoons is a vaccinia rabies glycoprotein (VRG) recombinant
that is being used for wild-life immunization. This vaccine is USDA
approved but can not be bought by individuals but rather by state officials.

